# Video Lock System

## Overview

The Video Lock system prevents simultaneous video watching across devices.

Goal:

- Prevent account sharing
- Prevent multiple simultaneous viewers

---

# Video Lock Rules

A user:

- Can watch only one video session at a time

If another device attempts playback:

→ Playback is blocked

---

# Video Lock APIs

Start video session:

```text
POST /api/security/video/start/
```

Stop video session:

```text
POST /api/security/video/stop/
```

Check video status:

```text
GET /api/security/video/status/
```

---

# Frontend Video Lock Integration

The frontend automatically:

- Starts video lock when lesson opens
- Stops lock when changing lessons
- Stops lock when leaving the page
- Stops lock when refreshing browser

---

# Browser Exit Handling

The frontend uses:

```javascript
navigator.sendBeacon();
```

Purpose:

- Ensure video lock cleanup
- Prevent stuck sessions
- Improve session reliability

---

# Video Lock User Experience

If playback is blocked:

The user sees:

- Lock message
- Error state
- Friendly explanation

Example:

```text
This account may already be watching a video on another device.
```

