# Signed Playback System

## Overview

Signed Playback prevents:

- Direct video URL sharing
- Unauthorized playback
- External playback attempts

Each playback requires:

- Temporary signed token

---

# Playback Security Flow

Frontend requests:

```text
GET /api/lessons/{lesson_id}/mux-token/
```

Backend:

- Validates user access
- Validates enrollment
- Validates permissions
- Generates signed JWT token

Frontend:

- Uses token with MuxPlayer

---

# Signed Token Generation

## File

```text
courses/services/mux_signed_token.py
```

The system uses:

```python
jwt.encode()
```

Algorithm:

```text
RS256
```

---

# Signed Playback Security Features

Playback tokens include:

- Playback ID
- Expiration time
- Audience validation
- Signing key validation

---

# Token Expiration

Playback tokens are temporary.

Example duration:

```text
10 minutes
```

Benefits:

- Reduced token reuse
- Better playback security
- Harder URL sharing

---

